A '''Force net''' was an unusual [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Force power/Legends|technique]]. When used successfully this power would summon [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] strands of energy that would wrap around the target and ensnare it in an unbreakable mesh. The lattice of dark energy would then effectively sever the connection between [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], and the trapped target, regardless of Force affiliation, and continuously sap the target's strength. After this, the energy lines would proceed to slice through anything they touched. The net was maintained through the recitation of certain words.

This technique was employed by [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Lomi Plo]] to kill a [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Shaper caste|shaper]] during the [[Mission to Myrkr]] and later during [[Swarm War]] in [[Battle of Sarm]] when she [[Lightsaber duel/Legends|dueled]] with [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. Once her victim had been ensnared, Lomi constricted the net, slicing up her victim. It was also used to torture and attempt to kill [[Ben Skywalker]] by [[Lost Tribe of Sith|Lost Tribe of the Sith]] [[High Lord (Circle of Lords)|High Lord]] [[Sarasu Taalon]] during the [[Battle in the Fallanassi village|fight]] with [[Abeloth]] on [[Pydyr]].<ref name="V">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Vortex]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Force net first appeared in the ''[[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order]]'' series.<ref name="SBS" />

